  <heading>STRH (register)</heading>
  <desc>
    <brief>
      <para>Store Register Halfword (register)</para>
    </brief>
    <authored>
      <para>Store Register Halfword (register) calculates an address from a base register value and an offset register value, and stores a halfword from a 32-bit register to the calculated address. For information about memory accesses, see <xref linkend="CHDIIIBB">Load/Store addressing modes</xref>.</para>
      <para>The instruction uses an offset addressing mode, that calculates the address used for the memory access from a base register value and an offset register value. The offset can be optionally shifted and extended.</para>
    </authored>
  </desc>
  <operationalnotes>
    <para>If PSTATE.DIT is 1, the timing of this instruction is insensitive to the value of the data being loaded or stored.</para>
  </operationalnotes>
